A git hook to check coding standards before a commit.

The following checks (which may be individually disabled) are performed:
   * Non-ASCII character file names
   * Compliance with uncrustify coding standards
   * Line lengths greater than 80 characters
   * Tab characters
   * Trailing whitespace
   * DOS line endings
   * Copyright check

Read the comment header block of pre-commit for a full explanation of this
pre-commit script.
